%% Source mermaid du schéma 2 — séquence complète de la démo attaque/défense (./demo.sh)
%% Régénérer le PNG : https://mermaid.live (export PNG) ou mermaid.ink
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as Toi (./demo.sh)
    participant K8s as Cluster Kubernetes (kind)
    participant Kyv as Webhook Kyverno (garde-barriere)

    rect rgb(255, 248, 220)
    Note over U,K8s: Phase 1 : Scenario nominal
    U->>K8s: kubectl apply deployment.yaml (image signee @sha256)
    K8s->>Kyv: Interception de la creation des Pods
    Kyv->>Kyv: Verifie signature + attestations
    Kyv-->>K8s: OK (signature et provenance valides)
    K8s-->>U: Succes : 2 Pods Running ✅
    end

    rect rgb(255, 235, 220)
    Note over U,K8s: Phase 2 : Attaque image NON SIGNEE
    U->>K8s: kubectl run pirate-unsigned --image=...:unsigned
    K8s->>Kyv: Interception du Pod
    Kyv->>Kyv: Cherche une signature du digest
    Kyv-->>K8s: REJET (no signatures found)
    K8s-->>U: Erreur : admission refusee 🛡️
    end

    rect rgb(255, 235, 220)
    Note over U,K8s: Phase 3 : Attaques tag :latest et registry externe
    U->>K8s: kubectl run pirate-latest --image=...:latest
    K8s->>Kyv: Interception du Pod
    Kyv-->>K8s: REJET (signature absente + disallow-latest-tag)
    U->>K8s: kubectl run pirate-registry --image=nginx:alpine
    K8s->>Kyv: Interception du Pod
    Kyv-->>K8s: REJET (allowed-registries : registry non autorise)
    K8s-->>U: Erreur : admissions refusees 🛡️
    end

    rect rgb(255, 220, 220)
    Note over U,K8s: Phase 4 : Attaque image MODIFIEE APRES SIGNATURE (backdoor)
    U->>K8s: kubectl run pirate-tampered --image=...:1.0.0-tampered
    K8s->>Kyv: Interception du Pod
    Kyv->>Kyv: Digest different : signature invalide
    Kyv-->>K8s: REJET (no signatures found)
    K8s-->>U: Erreur : image alteree bloquee — integrite garantie 🛡️
    end
